<title>SRI LANKA: Commercial up on broad-based buying.</title>
<headline>Commercial up on broad-based buying.</headline>
<dateline>COLOMBO 1997-01-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Commercial Bank Ltd was 6.67 percent or 10 rupees up at 160 on buying of 5,000 shares by local institutional and retail investors, brokers said.</p>
<p>&quot;Institutions are buying because the share offers good value at current levels. Retail investors are buying on speculation on news that a number of people are after a big parcel of the bank's shares,&quot; said a local broker.</p>
</text>
